### The `route()` Factory — Core API

**Found in**: `/Users/taras/worktrees/agent-swarm/2026-03-18-linear/src/http/route-def.ts`

The `route()` function accepts a `RouteDef` object and returns a `RouteHandle` with two methods:
- **`match(method, pathSegments)`** — returns `boolean` if the request matches this route
- **`parse(req, res, pathSegments, queryParams)`** — validates params/query/body via Zod; returns parsed data or `null` (and sends 400 automatically on validation failure)

It also registers the route into a global `routeRegistry` array (used by OpenAPI generation).

Key `RouteDef` fields:
```typescript
{
  method: "get" | "post" | "put" | "delete" | "patch",
  path: string,             // OpenAPI-style: "/api/tasks/{id}"
  pattern: (string|null)[], // matchRoute-style: ["api","tasks",null] — null = dynamic param
  exact?: boolean,          // default true
  summary: string,
  description?: string,
  tags: string[],
  params?: z.ZodType,       // path params (extracted from null slots in pattern)
  query?: z.ZodType,        // query string params
  body?: z.ZodType,         // JSON body
  responses: Record<number, { description: string; schema?: z.ZodType }>,
  auth?: { apiKey?: boolean; agentId?: boolean },
}
```

